org.youscope.common.table

Interface TableListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.EventListener, java.rmi.Remote
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TableDataAdapter

    public interface TableListener
extends java.rmi.Remote, java.util.EventListener
    Listener which can be registered at a table producing measurement component to get informed when new table data was produced. See Table for more information about the produced table.
    Author:
    Moritz Lang

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void newTableProduced(Table table)
      Gets called when a new table was produced by the table producer.

    • Method Detail

      • newTableProduced

        void newTableProduced(Table table)
               throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Gets called when a new table was produced by the table producer. For measurement components (e.g. Job), this function should be called for every listener exactly once per evaluation. This includes calling this function even with a Table containing no rows.
        Parameters:
        table - The produced table.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException
